"And if your waterways present a significant shortcut between your road "
"networks, your economy will tend to send many wares over the waterway. As a "
"waterway can hold only one ferry – unlike roads, which receive a second "
"carrier if they are very busy –, and as they often tend to be rather longer "
"than the two or three fields recommended for roads, there is always a risk "
"of waterways becoming severe bottlenecks in your economy. Try to build "
"several of them in parallel to distribute the strain. If this is not "
"possible, it is in some cases even more efficient not to use waterways."
msgstr "Agus ma bhios na slighean aiseig agad mòran nas giorra na na rathaidean agad, cuiridh an eaconamaidh tòrr bhatharan tromhpa. Air sgàth ’s nach eil ach aon bhàta-aiseig aig gach slighe aiseig – eucoltach ri rathaidean aig a bheil dithis ma tha iad glè thrang – agus on a bhios iad a’ sìneadh nas fhaide eadar nam bratach na bhios rathaidean mar as trice, tha cunnart ann gun dèid slighe aiseig ’na bhealach cumhang dhan eaconamaidh agad. Feuch an tog thu grunn dhiubh ri taobh càch a chèile airson an t-eallach a chom-pàirteachadh. Mura gabh sin a dhèanamh, dh’fhaodte gum bi e nas èifeachdaiche gun a bhith a’ cleachdadh slighe aiseig."
